#1988 - #FortLauderdale #Florida
On December 27, 1988, this woman was found dead behind a convenience store at 5190 South State Road 7, in unincorporated area near Fort Lauderdale, Florida.
Her death was due to an accidental cocaine overdose. Her body had been dumped at the location.
She was between 25 and 40 years old, was 5 feet 4 inches tall, and 108 lbs. She had very curly shoulder-length reddish brown hair and either brown, greyish brown, or hazel eyes (different sites describe her eye color differently)
She had a #tattoo of a blue #butterfly on her frontal pelvic area.
26 years later, she remains #UNIDENTIFIED.
